public class FloatLongScatterMap
extends FloatLongHashMap
    Same as FloatLongHashMap but does not implement per-instance key mixing strategy and uses a simpler (faster) bit distribution function.

    Note: read about important differences between hash and scatter sets.

    • Method Detail

      • hashKey

        protected int hashKey(float key)
        Description copied from class: FloatLongHashMap
        Returns a hash code for the given key.

        The default implementation mixes the hash of the key with FloatLongHashMap.keyMixer to differentiate hash order of keys between hash containers. Helps alleviate problems resulting from linear conflict resolution in open addressing.

        The output from this function should evenly distribute keys across the entire integer range.
